Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.03,0:00:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma and I were so worried
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.66,0:00:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about her Bible study, Palesa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.08,0:00:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,She had spent another sleepless night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.33,0:00:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,after again hearing\Nher dead grandmother’s voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.29,0:00:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,plus the sound of slamming doors\Nand items crashing in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.60,0:00:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Palesa had put an amulet\Non her baby’s wrist for protection,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.52,0:00:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but the terror continued all night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.65,0:00:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it wasn’t really her grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.94,0:00:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing in the house was broken;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.70,0:00:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but the attack was real.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.33,0:01:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Stories about the spirit world weren’t new to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.88,0:01:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Our neighbors, the people I work with,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.30,0:01:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the people in our territory
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.34,0:01:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,—almost everyone believes in spirits,\Nwhether they admit it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.89,0:01:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,No—more than believe—they fear them!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.81,0:01:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I had only been studying the Bible\Nabout six months longer than Palesa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.69,0:01:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But my study had proved to me\Nthat wicked spirits are here on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.03,0:01:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that they try to interact with people,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.95,0:01:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they are dangerous enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.21,0:01:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma called the elders for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.87,0:01:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn’t want us to handle\Nthe situation on our own.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.26,0:01:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As Emma told the story,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.51,0:02:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to speak up and tell the elders\Nthat she was leaving things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.31,0:02:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But I was surprised when the elders\Nsaid they didn’t need all the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.32,0:02:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They explained that while we are aware\Nof the danger the demons pose,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.32,0:02:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,we do not spend time\Ntalking about their activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.28,0:02:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Jesus, when he was on earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.20,0:02:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,could have told his disciples many stories
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.21,0:02:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about the doings of wicked spirits,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.96,0:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but instead,\Nhe focused on Jehovah and His activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.96,0:02:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We should do the same
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.17,0:02:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of telling stories about what the demons
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.51,0:02:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,may or may not have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.01,0:02:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders skillfully used the Bible,\Nshepherding everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.48,0:02:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We read Ephesians 6:11:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.23,0:02:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Put on the complete suit of armor from God
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.65,0:02:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“so that you may be able to stand firm
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,against the crafty acts of the Devil.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Those instructions were so important.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.08,0:03:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A soldier would be vulnerable\Nif he only wore part of his armor
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.08,0:03:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or if he didn’t keep it in good repair.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.34,0:03:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we read Ephesians 4:27:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.47,0:03:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not give the Devil an opportunity.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.52,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders explained to Palesa
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.52,0:03:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that the string around her daughter’s wrist
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is not part of the armor from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.44,0:03:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it is giving Satan\Nan opportunity to continue to harass the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.86,0:03:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The brothers reminded us\Nthat anyone who wants Jehovah’s protection
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,must completely break free
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from anything associated with superstition,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.50,0:03:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritism, and demon worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.13,0:03:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would ever choose to side\Nwith wicked spirits instead of with Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.76,0:04:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma reminded Palesa\Nof how urgent the situation was.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.48,0:04:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But only Palesa could decide what she would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.12,0:04:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be a loyal servant of Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.58,0:04:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why I’m getting baptized.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.34,0:04:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve decided not to listen to or tell
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.55,0:04:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,any more stories about the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.17,0:04:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But more than that,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.18,0:04:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to look at other parts of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I doing anything\Nthat would “give the Devil an opportunity”?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.31,0:05:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly,\Nthere are still changes I need to make.
